{"componentChunkName":"component---src-page-post-tsx","path":"/working-remote-quality-together-time","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Markus Tacker","tagLine":"Software Crafter","description":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at Nordic Semiconductor.‚Äã\n\t\tMentor. Speaker. ‚ÄãConference & Community builder. Camper. üèïÔ∏è üöê","gitHubUrl":"https://github.com/coderbyheart/coderbyheart.com.git","siteUrl":"https://coderbyheart.com","twitter":"@coderbyheart","defaultCard":"https://images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/3Jk4P6nFPNzaz1gsguktk8/350b7e4ddb2c7d86416243d9902920e2/social-card-default-2020.png"}}},"pageContext":{"page":{"id":"ff472cdd-1fc6-5426-890a-e97210707b06","name":"working-remote-quality-together-time","relativeDirectory":"post","relativePath":"post/working-remote-quality-together-time.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"This post series is a summary of my talk about the challenge working in\ndistributed teams.\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Find the other parts here."}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"./working-in-distributed-teams-the-three-most-important-challenges/"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The few times you spend together with your employees face to face should be\nquality time!"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"If you have\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"fixed the missing watercooler"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"./working-remote-fix-the-missing-watercooler/"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\nyou are still not learning much about the personal quirks everyone has, but this\nis important for a good understanding of each others motivations and fears.\nThat‚Äôs why you simply must bring everyone together regularly, at least every\nother month. Yes, this requires a lot of effort and it costs money! And to focus\non getting everyone to know each other better, this occasion should not be spent\nwith business-as-usual activities."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Focus on activities that require interaction and profit off physical presence\nwhich is doing retrospectives, doing 1-on-1s or even lunch and dinner."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"For us it worked best to have all-hands on Tuesday and Wednesday. The remotees\nwould travel on Monday and Thursday which left the weekend untouched for them\nand also prices for flights are lower if you don‚Äôt travel on fridays or the\nweekends."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"And this is the important part: you need to make sure that they feel the effort\nof traveling is worth it."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#protip-4-plan-every-hour---make-their-stay-worthwile","ariaLabel":"protip 4 plan every hour   make their stay worthwile permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Protip #4: Plan every hour - make their stay worthwile!"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"protip-4-plan-every-hour---make-their-stay-worthwile","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"When bringing people together for an all-hands meeting it is important to not\nonly take care of their activities during the day but the complete trip has to\nbe planned and prepared in advance. You need to be their host! This may sound\nsuperfluous but I for me this is an import part of making room for the\nconnection building part that is the purpose of these events."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Take care of their individual travel preferences."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Let them arrive on the afternoon before so they are relaxed when the all-hands\nstarts."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Pick them up on arrival because they are usually not accustomed to the local\nmodes of transportation. Also take care of their departure!"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Organize for their accomodation: staying with colleagues is awesome, but make\nthis opt-in only, not everyone likes having people at their homes or staying\nover at other peoples places. Pay for hotels and don‚Äôt force them to share\nrooms."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Plan the days but also the evening activities."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ul","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"An important side note: especially remote work is attractive for people that are\nintroverts. Therefore it is important for every group activity you plan to keep\nthis in mind. You should always find a polite way to offer everyone a way to\nopt-out of an activity or provide an alternative that allows them to recharge."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#coming-up-celebrate-successes","ariaLabel":"coming up celebrate successes permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Coming up: celebrate successes"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"coming-up-celebrate-successes","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],